gov.usgs.adslserver.utility

Class ISCLoader2

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.adslserver.utility.ISCLoader2

  • public class ISCLoader2
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the backup of the original ISCLoader code before it was refactored to be better for maintainance. This class reads a ascii dllist file generated by the ISC with registered codes and runs it through the IRServerRow process to decide if it needs to be added to the IRServer and creates IRServer station records, initial locatione epochs, etc. for all station unknown to the IRServer database (many station were probably loaded by dataless imports or ANSS spread sheet file). Additionally for ANSS loaded stations, this file contains elevations that were not on the spread sheet so those are updated in the location records for ANSS stations The IRlist.txt looks like : 1 AAM AAM 42.3012 -83.6567 172.0 1940-01-01 00:00:00 1 GWDE IR 38.8284 -75.6171 19.0 1995-08-29 00:00:00 2 GWDE IR 38.8284 -75.6171 19.0 1995-08-29 00:00:00 2001-06-29 00:00:00 3 GWDE IR 38.8256 -75.6171 19.0 1995-08-29 00:00:00 2001-06-29 00:00:00 ? stat agency lat lon elev depth prime Open date close data
